With just five working days to go before what would otherwise have been its D-Day, the Commission of Inquiry into Allegations of State Capture was yesterday thrown a lifeline by the court. This, with Judge Wendy Hughes, sitting in the North Gauteng High Court in Pretoria, extending the commission’s deadline to complete its work, to 31 March 2021. Despite the commission’s opposition, though, she made the extension final. “In my view, further extensions would not be warranted on the [commission’s] version,” Judge Hughes said in handing down her ruling, “The interest of justice dictates that finality be attained with findings,...